    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look for offensive consistency today, led by **Jackson Merrill**, who anchors the lineup with an elite 67.37 score. Despite facing a tough test in Luis Castillo, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a strong platoon advantage and a premium #2 spot in the order, making him our highest-ceiling play. **Jacob Wilson** also provides significant value (62.77) thanks to a favorable park environment and a middle-of-the-order projection against Jack Leiter. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.05) remains a staple, the day\u2019s most intriguing volatility involves **Gunnar Henderson** (47.79). Though his raw projections remain solid, he faces a double-whammy of a difficult matchup against Parker Messick and a 44% rain risk in the forecast, necessitating close monitoring as we approach first pitch.\n\nOur bench decision-making process was tightest at the corner infield spots, where **Brady House** (47.22) narrowly missed the starting cut. While **Brady House** carries an intriguing profile against Ashcraft, the decision to favor **Josh Jung** (51.04) and **Miguel Vargas** (50.05) was driven by **Miguel Vargas**\u2019s optimal leadoff positioning against Steven Matz and **Josh Jung**\u2019s favorable park factors. We are prioritizing on-base stability over the upside of **Brady House** or **Nolan Schanuel** (46.83) today, as we attempt to maximize category production without overextending our game cap exposure. We continue to hold **Nasim Nunez** and **Coby Mayo** in reserve, keeping a close eye on their lineup statuses should any late scratches force a pivot in our offensive strategy.",
